le correlations with $R_{\\rm e}$ and\nvelocity dispersions are more robust. Our results clearly point to a\n\"non-homology\" in the total mass distribution of ETGs, which simulations of\ngalaxy formation suggest may be related to a varying role of dissipation with\ngalaxy mass.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 1 Sep 2014 20:00:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-22"}
